<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES70-5 - DISASSEMBLE - SHIFT
        TOWER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Standard Shift Tower</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301102">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301102" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301102" filename="../figg13/g1301102.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Standard Shift Tower - Exploded View</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HANDLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LEVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. ROCK SHAFT PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. GASKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. LEVER HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. SNAP RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. LEVER COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. SPRING RETAINER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts and lock- washers. Separate the lever housing from the
                    shifter housing and gasket. Lift it straight up.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position shift lever housing on edge in a vise.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press the spring retainer against the spring. Remove the lock pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide lever cover up the shift lever and remove the rock shaft snap ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tap the rock shaft free of the lever housing and remove the shift lever. Remove and
                    discard the gasket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift lever handle. Slide lever cover, spring retainer and spring off
                    lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash all parts thoroughly and inspect the lever and rock shaft cross holes for excessive
                    wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check spring tension by comparing the old spring to a new one. Replace if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
